FBIS4-6622 "dreas078_a_94017" FBIS-EAS-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Hosokawa Denies Role in Income Report Failure Hosokawa Denies Role in Income Report Failure OW2204125194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1226 GMT 22 Apr 94 OW2204125194 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Excerpt] Tokyo, April 22 KYODO -- Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa said Friday [22 April] he did not personally have a hand in a failure to report some 29 million yen of his personal income to tax authorities. "It is common for legislators to have their offices handle accounting and raising of funds, including their personal funds," Hosokawa said. Hosokawa's chief political secretary, Namio Yatsuka, told a news conference earlier in the day that the prime minister did not disclose the 29 million yen income from stock and bond investment during a 10-year period from 1981. [passage omitted]
